Sentence: Ses01F_impro04_M000 [002.7418-006.6575]: Have you tried, uh, Craig's List?
Isn't that-- that's all like escort services and things like that.
I mean I've been looking for so long that I just figured that--  I mean, I think things like Monster are a lot more reliable than just some random free board.
Ses01F_impro04_M004 [030.8800-035.5225]: I'm just saying I have a friend that got a good job on it so I was just recommending it.
Ses01F_impro04_F003 [035.0090-037.8000]: What kind of a job?
Ses01F_impro04_M005 [037.1900-040.5300]: He's like a manager for a theatre.
Ses01F_impro04_M006 [040.5400-043.5760]: He's like a house manager.
I saw a posting at the theatre.
Ses01F_impro04_M009 [056.3500-059.0245]: You've been looking for a job for a long time; that was a long time ago.
I don't understand why they would pick him over me.
He had a really good resume I guess and--
Ses01F_impro04_M013 [073.7473-077.1500]: It's kind of helpful when getting a job.
Ses01F_impro04_F013 [076.4900-080.7269]: I just- I mean I call people up and I tell them what I'm good at.
Ses01F_impro04_M014 [080.1435-087.8100]: Well maybe we should sit down some time and you can just tell me all the stuff that you have done and I'll write it out.
Ses01F_impro04_F015 [087.2203-093.3300]: I don't like- I don't like sending things in the mail.
I don't want my information out there.
You can- or you can just bring it in person.
But they need, generally, something to see, you know, what kind of what that you've done, what kind of--
Ses01F_impro04_F016 [097.4100-101.0475]: I'm there in front of them.
I'm telling them what I'm good at.
But the piece of paper helps, too.
But it has an outline, you know.
Ses01F_impro04_F018 [106.1700-111.8600]: I just don't want this paper trail, you know.
I just don't want things following me around, like-.
Ses01F_impro04_F019 [114.9200-122.3100]: It's just-- You know, I've had this problem before.
You're not the first person to tell me that I need a resume but...
Ses01F_impro04_F020 [122.4000-129.9300]: ..I just-..I just think it's kind of prejudiced and they are really discriminating against people who just aren't that way.
Ses01F_impro04_M021 [129.4300-139.1600]: Well, sometimes you have to do things that you don't necessarily like to do to have a job.
But the job affords you money, you won't have to be taking the bus right now.
Ses01F_impro04_M023 [144.9125-149.5100]: I just, you know, think you should try a little harder maybe.
Ses01F_impro04_F023 [148.5500-152.8500]: you think that you're better than me because I don't have a car?
Ses01F_impro04_F024 [153.1800-155.2925]: You know, you're riding the bus, too.
Ses01F_impro04_M025 [154.6000-157.8000]: I am riding the bus, but by choice.
Ses01F_impro04_M026 [158.9500-161.3500]: To save the environment, carpool.
One less car at a time.
Ses01F_impro04_M029 [167.0500-171.4300]: You know, you don't have to take out your frustration on me, you know, just because...
Ses01F_impro04_M030 [171.7500-175.2600]: ...you can't get a job and refuse to have a resume.
Ses01F_impro04_F029 [175.2700-178.4300]: Who do you think you are?
Ses01F_impro04_M031 [178.0033-180.8650]: I don't think I'm anyone.
Ses01F_impro04_F030 [180.3025-183.4875]: You are so high and mighty.
I'm riding this car because I- I want to.
Ses01F_impro04_F032 [189.1200-192.0200]: The bus, I'm riding the bus because I want to.
You don't have to take your anger and your hurt out on me.
Ses01F_impro04_F033 [193.5875-199.4325]: I can not-- you are not here by choice.
Nobody would ride this bus by choice.
